definition: to become invalid/to cancel/to delete/to nullify
to do/to grow/to write or compose/to pretend/to regard as/to feel/writings or works
to abolish/to abandon/to abrogate/to discard/to depose/to oust/crippled/abandoned/waste

sentences.english: None were cancelled or lapsed during the period.
sentences.chinese: 於期內，概無任何購股權遭註銷或作廢。

sentences.english: Often if such a trade-off exists, it nullifies the study results.
sentences.chinese: 通常這種權衡一出現，研究結果就算作廢了。

sentences.english: This is only first-time registration. Otherwises, the registration will be cancelled.
sentences.chinese: 祗適用於首次登記，否則登記可能會被作廢。

sentences.english: It now may be scrapped or altered.
sentences.chinese: 現在這樁交易可能作廢或更改。

sentences.english: It was thought that the rediscovery of Mendelian inheritance invalidated Darwin's views.
sentences.chinese: 據認爲，孟德爾遺傳的重新發現使達爾文的觀點作廢。

sentences.english: Banya membership card will become invalid automatically if it is not used within 12 months.
sentences.chinese: 班雅會員卡在12個月內無使用記錄，則自動作廢。

sentences.english: An alien who has lost his /her residence card shall declare the lost card invalid in an official local newspaper.
sentences.chinese: 遺失外國人居留證的，須在當地政府報紙上聲明作廢。

sentences.english: The number of days after a password expires until the account is permanently disabled.
sentences.chinese: 指定帳號密碼過期的時間到帳號永久作廢的天數。

sentences.english: His proposal was diluted by the lack of support from the Security Council.
sentences.chinese: 他的建議由於缺乏安理會的支持而作廢了。

sentences.english: We will void the existing and issue a new one.
sentences.chinese: 我們將把現有的票作廢，然後再出一張新票。

sentences.english: Keep GPA stable, and avoid pre-admissions to be finally cancelled.
sentences.chinese: 避免預錄取最終被取消或作廢。

sentences.english: If either fails to achieve a two-thirds majority in favor of the legislation, the bill dies.
sentences.chinese: 如果任何一院達不到三分之二多數，提案就將作廢。

sentences.english: The government retires worn or torn bills from use.
sentences.chinese: 政府將破損的鈔票收回作廢。

sentences.english: A lot of what we do can easily be nullified by greed and tribal warfare.
sentences.chinese: 我們做的很多事情都很可能因貪婪和部落鬥爭而作廢。

sentences.english: When prenumbering exists, all voided documents should be retained.
sentences.chinese: 如果憑證是事先編碼的，所有作廢的憑證都應該保留。

sentences.english: Don't spoil your ballot by writing in the wrong place.
sentences.chinese: 不要填錯位子，使得你的選票作廢。

definition: to return (sth borrowed etc)/to send back/to refund/to rebate
to break a promise/breach of contract
to bear joint responsibility for sth/joint liability (law)
to order goods/to place an order
to repay a debt in full/to redeem/to clear
